==Ground transport==
The airport is situated {{convert|16|km|sp=us}} by road from the city center. [[Norwegian National Road 451|National Road 451]] runs along the northern side of the runway and connects to [[Norwegian National Road 41|National Road 41]]. It connects to the [[European route E18|E18]] freeway.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://avinor.no/en/airport/kristiansand-airport/to-and-from-the-airport/#!by-car-1050 |title=By car |publisher=[[Avinor]] |accessdate=27 December 2014}}</ref> The airport features parking for 1,800 cars.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://avinor.no/en/airport/kristiansand-airport/to-and-from-the-airport/#!parkering-1055 |title=Parking |publisher=[[Avinor]] |accessdate=27 December 2014}}</ref> Car rental is also available.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://avinor.no/en/airport/kristiansand-airport/to-and-from-the-airport/#!car-rental-1051 |title=Car rental |publisher=[[Avinor]] |accessdate=27 December 2014}}</ref>

Haga Buss operates an airport coach to Kristiansand. [[Nettbuss]] operates a coach service to [[Lillesand]], [[Grimstad]] and [[Arendal]]. This is a direct service during rush hour and a shuttle service from a stop on the [[European route E18|E18]] the rest of the day. Agder Flyekspress operates a direct coach service to Arendal. Taxis are available at the airport.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://avinor.no/flyplass/kristiansand/til-og-fra-flyplassen/#!buss-og-taxi-1049 |title=Buss og taxi |publisher=[[Avinor]] |accessdate=27 December 2014 |language=Norwegian}}</ref>

